race.comment: SILVER WEDDING (5) sets up well with the fast pace assured second-up. Slow into stride on resumption and struck trouble in the straight with the 59.5kg when a respectable fifth over 1100m at Warwick Farm. Has come back well and can easily finish over the top of them. SPIRIT OF WEALTH (6) came out fast in the five-horse field with the 61kg when a slick winner over 1100m at Hawkesbury against inferior opposition. Must raise the bar today and gets her chance. WEEPING WOMAN (2) raced quickly through her grades last prep and resumes with a solid record at this trip. Readied for this with the two trials and the booking of Rawiller is a good lead. KIMBERLEY SECRETS (3) tough country mare holding her own in town in easier company. Comes here deep into the prep with the 3kg claim. Can surprise some of her more fancied rivals. TAXATION (11) second of the Pride runners undefeated in two starts. Can sit off them and handle the steep rise in class.
